    • denyAccess

      protected boolean denyAccess(org.bukkit.command.CommandSender actor, String... permissions)
      Deprecated.
      Checks if the user has at least one of the provided permissions. This will send a message to the player which uses the error.permission locale key which should provide a placeholder PERMISSION for an array of required permissions, if the user lacks all of the permissions.
      Parameters:
      actor - actor which wants to execute this action
      permissions - one or more permissions to check
      Returns:
      true if the user has no of the required permission

    • denyAccess

      actor - actor which wants to execute this action
      silent - set to true if no message should be send to the player
